# shellcheck disable=SC2148
# This file specifies patterns for files and directories to be ignored by GNU Stow
# ------------------------------

# Comments and blank lines are allowed

RCS
.+,v

CVS
\.\#.+       # CVS conflict files / emacs lock files
\.cvsignore

\.svn
_darcs
\.hg

\.git
\.gitignore
\.gitmodules

.+~          # emacs backup files
# \#.*\#       # emacs autosave files

^/README.md
^/LICENSE
^/COPYING

# Ignore standard user folders
/Desktop
/Documents
/Downloads
/Music
/Pictures
/Videos
/Templates
/Public
/Library
/Applications
/Movies

# Ignore user-specific and system files
#
# Note:
#   Do NOT ignore `/.config`, `/.local`, or `/.cache` globally.
#   This repo may stow files into ~/.config (e.g. starship.toml) in the future.
#   If you want to avoid stowing a specific subtree, ignore it more narrowly.
/.CFUserTextEncoding
/.zsh_history
/.bash_history
/.lmstudio
/.vscode
/.zsh_sessions
/.DS_Store
/.Trash

# Ignore stow control files
.stowrc
\.macos
\.fedora

# Ignore installation and script files (not meant to be stowed)
/install.sh
install.sh
^/scripts
\Brewfile


# Example configuration files (not meant to be stowed)
\example\.conf
\example\.jpg
\example\.png
\example\.txt
\example\.md

# Ignore VS Code extensions — these are managed by VS Code, not stow.
# We only want to stow settings.json, argv.json, etc.
\.vscode/extensions
\.vscode/cli

# Note:
#   Do NOT ignore files such as .editorconfig here.
#   Those live under the `common/` stow package and should be linked.
